  stickyNoteInfos:
  - title: 0-1 Line Sequencer
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 5132
      y: -7192
      width: 310
      height: 218
    contents: "Calculating a normalized 0-1 spawnIndex for our particles is often
      very useful as it can be used to sample curves, distribute particles' size,
      position, etc.\n\r\nAs we're spawning 5 particles, the Spawn Index attribute
      will range from 0-4.\r\n\r\nNormalize 0-1 spawnIndex= spawn Index / (Number
      of particles - 1.0) \r\nThis 0-1 value is used in a line sequencer to distribute
      the particles along the line.\r\n"
    theme: 
    textSize: Small
    colorTheme: 2
  - title: TexIndex
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 6593
      y: -6968
      width: 419
      height: 119
    contents: 'Our U, N, I, T, and Y letters are inside a sprite sheet.

      We''re
      spawning 5 particles and using their spawn index, which ranges from 0 to 4,
      to set our texIndex. By doing so, each particle gets assigned a different letter
      in our Sprite Sheet.

'
    theme: 
    textSize: Small
    colorTheme: 3
  - title: 'Offset Animation:'
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 4518
      y: -5824
      width: 230
      height: 101
    contents: 'The spawnIndex is used to delay the start of the size and color attribute
      animations.

      This is what makes each letter appear one after the other.

'
    theme: 
    textSize: Small
    colorTheme: 2
  - title: Unity Font
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 6130
      y: -7949
      width: 456
      height: 107
    contents: 
    theme: 
    textSize: Huge
    colorTheme: 2
  - title: Global Spawn EVENT
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 7129
      y: -8727
      width: 840
      height: 107
    contents: 
    theme: 
    textSize: Huge
    colorTheme: 2
  categories: []
  uiBounds:
    serializedVersion: 2
    x: 4493
    y: -8727
    width: 3476
    height: 4084
